26// The maximum allowed value for a timestamp in milliseconds. This is lower
27// than the numerical limit since we often convert to microseconds.
28static constexpr int64_t kMaxTimeMs =
29 std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max() / 1000;
30
31RemoteEstimatorProxy::RemoteEstimatorProxy(
32 Clock* clock,
33 TransportFeedbackSender feedback_sender,
34 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* key_value_config,
35 NetworkStateEstimator* network_state_estimator)
36 : clock_(clock),
37 feedback_sender_(std::move(feedback_sender)),
38 send_config_(key_value_config),
39 last_process_time_ms_(-1),
40 network_state_estimator_(network_state_estimator),
41 media_ssrc_(0),
42 feedback_packet_count_(0),
43 send_interval_ms_(send_config_.default_interval->ms()),
44 send_periodic_feedback_(true),
45 previous_abs_send_time_(0),
46 abs_send_timestamp_(clock->CurrentTime()) {
47 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
48 << "Maximum interval between transport feedback RTCP messages (ms): "
49 << send_config_.max_interval->ms();
50}
51
52RemoteEstimatorProxy::~RemoteEstimatorProxy() {}
53
54void RemoteEstimatorProxy::MaybeCullOldPackets(int64_t sequence_number,
55 int64_t arrival_time_ms) {
56 if (periodic_window_start_seq_.has_value()) {
57 if (*periodic_window_start_seq_ >=
58 packet_arrival_times_.end_sequence_number()) {
59 // Start new feedback packet, cull old packets.
60 packet_arrival_times_.RemoveOldPackets(
61 sequence_number, arrival_time_ms - send_config_.back_window->ms());
62 }
63 }
64}
65
66void RemoteEstimatorProxy::IncomingPacket(int64_t arrival_time_ms,
67 size_t payload_size,
68 const RTPHeader& header) {
69 if (arrival_time_ms < 0 || arrival_time_ms > kMaxTimeMs) {
70 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Arrival time out of bounds: " << arrival_time_ms;
71 return;
72 }
73 MutexLock lock(&lock_);
74 media_ssrc_ = header.ssrc;
75 int64_t seq = 0;
76
77 if (header.extension.hasTransportSequenceNumber) {
78 seq = unwrapper_.Unwrap(header.extension.transportSequenceNumber);
79
80 if (send_periodic_feedback_) {
81 MaybeCullOldPackets(seq, arrival_time_ms);
82
83 if (!periodic_window_start_seq_ || seq < *periodic_window_start_seq_) {
84 periodic_window_start_seq_ = seq;
85 }
86 }
87
88 // We are only interested in the first time a packet is received.
89 if (packet_arrival_times_.has_received(seq)) {
90 return;
91 }
92
93 packet_arrival_times_.AddPacket(seq, arrival_time_ms);
94
95 // Limit the range of sequence numbers to send feedback for.
96 if (!periodic_window_start_seq_.has_value() ||
97 periodic_window_start_seq_.value() <
98 packet_arrival_times_.begin_sequence_number()) {
99 periodic_window_start_seq_ =
100 packet_arrival_times_.begin_sequence_number();
101 }
102
103 if (header.extension.feedback_request) {
104 // Send feedback packet immediately.
105 SendFeedbackOnRequest(seq, header.extension.feedback_request.value());
106 }
107 }
108
109 if (network_state_estimator_ && header.extension.hasAbsoluteSendTime) {
110 PacketResult packet_result;
111 packet_result.receive_time = Timestamp::Millis(arrival_time_ms);
112 // Ignore reordering of packets and assume they have approximately the
113 // same send time.
114 abs_send_timestamp_ += std::max(
115 header.extension.GetAbsoluteSendTimeDelta(previous_abs_send_time_),
116 TimeDelta::Millis(0));
117 previous_abs_send_time_ = header.extension.absoluteSendTime;
118 packet_result.sent_packet.send_time = abs_send_timestamp_;
119 // TODO(webrtc:10742): Take IP header and transport overhead into account.
120 packet_result.sent_packet.size =
121 DataSize::Bytes(header.headerLength + payload_size);
122 packet_result.sent_packet.sequence_number = seq;
123 network_state_estimator_->OnReceivedPacket(packet_result);
124 }
125}

127bool RemoteEstimatorProxy::LatestEstimate(std::vector<unsigned int>* ssrcs,
128 unsigned int* bitrate_bps) const {
129 return false;
130}
131
132int64_t RemoteEstimatorProxy::TimeUntilNextProcess() {
133 MutexLock lock(&lock_);
134 if (!send_periodic_feedback_) {
135 // Wait a day until next process.
136 return 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000;
137 } else if (last_process_time_ms_ != -1) {
138 int64_t now = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
139 if (now - last_process_time_ms_ < send_interval_ms_)
140 return last_process_time_ms_ + send_interval_ms_ - now;
141 }
142 return 0;
143}
144
145void RemoteEstimatorProxy::Process() {
146 MutexLock lock(&lock_);
147 if (!send_periodic_feedback_) {
148 return;
149 }
150 last_process_time_ms_ = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
151
152 SendPeriodicFeedbacks();
153}
154
155void RemoteEstimatorProxy::OnBitrateChanged(int bitrate_bps) {
156 // TwccReportSize = Ipv4(20B) + UDP(8B) + SRTP(10B) +
157 // AverageTwccReport(30B)
158 // TwccReport size at 50ms interval is 24 byte.
159 // TwccReport size at 250ms interval is 36 byte.
160 // AverageTwccReport = (TwccReport(50ms) + TwccReport(250ms)) / 2
161 constexpr int kTwccReportSize = 20 + 8 + 10 + 30;
162 const double kMinTwccRate =
163 kTwccReportSize * 8.0 * 1000.0 / send_config_.max_interval->ms();
164 const double kMaxTwccRate =
165 kTwccReportSize * 8.0 * 1000.0 / send_config_.min_interval->ms();
166
167 // Let TWCC reports occupy 5% of total bandwidth.
168 MutexLock lock(&lock_);
169 send_interval_ms_ = static_cast<int>(
170 0.5 + kTwccReportSize * 8.0 * 1000.0 /
171 rtc::SafeClamp(send_config_.bandwidth_fraction * bitrate_bps,
172 kMinTwccRate, kMaxTwccRate));
173}
174
175void RemoteEstimatorProxy::SetSendPeriodicFeedback(
176 bool send_periodic_feedback) {
177 MutexLock lock(&lock_);
178 send_periodic_feedback_ = send_periodic_feedback;
179}
180
181void RemoteEstimatorProxy::SendPeriodicFeedbacks() {
182 // |periodic_window_start_seq_| is the first sequence number to include in
183 // the current feedback packet. Some older may still be in the map, in case
184 // a reordering happens and we need to retransmit them.
185 if (!periodic_window_start_seq_)
186 return;
187
188 std::unique_ptr<rtcp::RemoteEstimate> remote_estimate;
189 if (network_state_estimator_) {
190 absl::optional<NetworkStateEstimate> state_estimate =
191 network_state_estimator_->GetCurrentEstimate();
192 if (state_estimate) {
193 remote_estimate = std::make_unique<rtcp::RemoteEstimate>();
194 remote_estimate->SetEstimate(state_estimate.value());
195 }
196 }
197
198 int64_t packet_arrival_times_end_seq =
199 packet_arrival_times_.end_sequence_number();
200 while (periodic_window_start_seq_ < packet_arrival_times_end_seq) {
201 auto feedback_packet = MaybeBuildFeedbackPacket(
202 /*include_timestamps=*/true, periodic_window_start_seq_.value(),
203 packet_arrival_times_end_seq,
204 /*is_periodic_update=*/true);
205
206 if (feedback_packet == nullptr) {
207 break;
208 }
209
210 RTC_DCHECK(feedback_sender_ != nullptr);
211
212 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<rtcp::RtcpPacket>> packets;
213 if (remote_estimate) {
214 packets.push_back(std::move(remote_estimate));
215 }
216 packets.push_back(std::move(feedback_packet));
217
218 feedback_sender_(std::move(packets));
219 // Note: Don't erase items from packet_arrival_times_ after sending, in
220 // case they need to be re-sent after a reordering. Removal will be
221 // handled by OnPacketArrival once packets are too old.
222 }
223}
224
225void RemoteEstimatorProxy::SendFeedbackOnRequest(
226 int64_t sequence_number,
227 const FeedbackRequest& feedback_request) {
228 if (feedback_request.sequence_count == 0) {
229 return;
230 }
231
232 int64_t first_sequence_number =
233 sequence_number - feedback_request.sequence_count + 1;
234
235 auto feedback_packet = MaybeBuildFeedbackPacket(
236 feedback_request.include_timestamps, first_sequence_number,
237 sequence_number + 1, /*is_periodic_update=*/false);
238
239 // This is called when a packet has just been added.
240 RTC_DCHECK(feedback_packet != nullptr);
241
242 // Clear up to the first packet that is included in this feedback packet.
243 packet_arrival_times_.EraseTo(first_sequence_number);
244
245 RTC_DCHECK(feedback_sender_ != nullptr);
246 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<rtcp::RtcpPacket>> packets;
247 packets.push_back(std::move(feedback_packet));
248 feedback_sender_(std::move(packets));
249}
250
251std::unique_ptr<rtcp::TransportFeedback>
252RemoteEstimatorProxy::MaybeBuildFeedbackPacket(
253 bool include_timestamps,
254 int64_t begin_sequence_number_inclusive,
255 int64_t end_sequence_number_exclusive,
256 bool is_periodic_update) {
257 RTC_DCHECK_LT(begin_sequence_number_inclusive, end_sequence_number_exclusive);
258
259 int64_t start_seq =
260 packet_arrival_times_.clamp(begin_sequence_number_inclusive);
261
262 int64_t end_seq = packet_arrival_times_.clamp(end_sequence_number_exclusive);
263
264 // Create the packet on demand, as it's not certain that there are packets
265 // in the range that have been received.
266 std::unique_ptr<rtcp::TransportFeedback> feedback_packet = nullptr;
267
268 int64_t next_sequence_number = begin_sequence_number_inclusive;
269
270 for (int64_t seq = start_seq; seq < end_seq; ++seq) {
271 int64_t arrival_time_ms = packet_arrival_times_.get(seq);
272 if (arrival_time_ms == 0) {
273 // Packet not received.
274 continue;
275 }
276
277 if (feedback_packet == nullptr) {
278 feedback_packet =
279 std::make_unique<rtcp::TransportFeedback>(include_timestamps);
280 // TODO(sprang): Measure receive times in microseconds and remove the
281 // conversions below.
282 feedback_packet->SetMediaSsrc(media_ssrc_);
283 // Base sequence number is the expected first sequence number. This is
284 // known, but we might not have actually received it, so the base time
285 // shall be the time of the first received packet in the feedback.
286 feedback_packet->SetBase(
287 static_cast<uint16_t>(begin_sequence_number_inclusive & 0xFFFF),
288 arrival_time_ms * 1000);
289 feedback_packet->SetFeedbackSequenceNumber(feedback_packet_count_++);
290 }
291
292 if (!feedback_packet->AddReceivedPacket(static_cast<uint16_t>(seq & 0xFFFF),
293 arrival_time_ms * 1000)) {
294 // Could not add timestamp, feedback packet might be full. Return and
295 // try again with a fresh packet.
296 break;
297 }
298
299 next_sequence_number = seq + 1;
300 }
301 if (is_periodic_update) {
302 periodic_window_start_seq_ = next_sequence_number;
303 }
304 return feedback_packet;
305}
